Commentary: A big, big appeal for LBW but turned down! Bowls it right in the blackhole with a bit of tail into the batter, on middle, James Anderson stays rooted in his crease as he looks to keep this one out. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! England gets the fourth wicket of the morning! Good low catch from Ben Foakes to dismiss the debutant Rajat Patidar! Rehan Ahmed drags the ball short just outside the off-stump line with no pace on offer. Rajat Patidar gets deep into the crease looking to cut the ball and capitalise on a loose delivery. The ball stays very low and turns away from Rajat Patidar. In order to adjust to the bounce, Rajat Patidar offers a half-hearted jab and gets an inside edge. Ben Foakes is equal to the task to pouch a healthy deflection as the ball nestles into the left glove to get rid of Rajat Patidar. The umpire raises his finger and India lose their fourth with a lead of 265.

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The debutant, Shoaib Bashir breaks through for England! First successful review of the series from England and what a time to get it right! Bashir offers flight and bowls it on off, Shubman Gill pulls out the reverse sweep but the ball is not that full to execute that shot. The ball does not turn much and it goes on to hit the gloves and lobs up only as far as the keeper. The England players think it has come off the pad and they appeal for LBW, which is turned down by the umpire. Amidst all this, the keeper, Ben Foakes is alert to the situation and sees the lobbing up. He takes it cleanly and then appeals for caught behind. The umpire is still unmoved and England take the review. There is a clear spike on the UltraEdge and the centurion will have to make the long way back. End of a special knock from a special player and he walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd and his teammates.
Default_Commentary: 55.6: Shoaib Bashir to Shubman Gill, OUT! c Ben Foakes b Shoaib Bashir.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Shoaib Bashir

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Excellent review and what a time to get it right! India get the wicket they desperately wanted and it is a massive blow to England just before Lunch! Kuldeep stays over the wicket and bowls it short and around the leg-stump line, Zak Crawley goes on the back foot to clip it away but misses to get pinged on the front pad. It looks to be turning sharply down leg and the umpire does not raise his finger. After a contemplation, Rohit Sharma goes for the review with not much left on the timer. Nothing on UltraEdge and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is not doing much and it is three reds on Ball Tracking. India are thrilled to bits and England have now lost half their side with still 205 runs away from victory!
Default_Commentary: 41.6: Kuldeep Yadav to Zak Crawley, OUT! lbw b Kuldeep Yadav.

It nipped back in sharply to trap Baristow in front and he looks gone for all money! Nothing on UltraEdge and it is clipping the leg stump on Ball Tracking. It is umpire's call and the on-field decision will stand. India go bang, bang just before Lunch and they find themselves in a commanding position! Bumrah stays from over the wicket and bowls it on a good length, tailing back in, on middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow stays leg side of the ball and opens himself up to access the off side. He fails to account for the inward movement and the ball jags back in to hit him above the knee roll on the back leg and it was enough to send him on his way. That will be LUNCH on DAY 4!

Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! Shreyas Iyer, you beauty! That should be the game for India! A body blow to England as their skipper pays the price for being lazy! Ashwin floats it up from around the wicket and bowls it full, on middle and leg, Ben Foakes presses forward to defend it away. Gets an inside edge onto the pads and it rolls to square leg. A yes-no situation for the single and Foakes is a bit late to get off the blocks. It is still an easy run but Ben Stokes is very casual in his approach and jogs most part of that run. He realises that the throw is coming at his end but the horse has bolted already. Shreyas Iyer swoops in and picks the ball up with hi right hand. He fires in a throw at the batting end and hits despite having only one stump to aim at. The replays show that Stokes had no part of his bat inside the crease when the throw hits the stumps. The Indian players gather around Shreyas Iyer and the crowd is as delighted as anything. India three wickets away now from making it 1-1!

Commentary: Another loud shout for LBW but Rohit Sharma indicates that it was doing too much and they do not take the review! Tailing in sharply, on a hard length, on middle and leg, Shoaib Bashir gets caught in his crease and gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball seams back in to hit him on the back pad.
Default_Commentary: 66.3: Jasprit Bumrah to Shoaib Bashir, No run.

Commentary: At pace and at the stumps, on a length, Shoaib Bashir stays leg side of the ball and stays low with the low bounce to stab it down on the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 66.4: Jasprit Bumrah to Shoaib Bashir, No run.

Commentary: NO BALL! Goes for the slower delivery but the ball slips out of his hand and drops beyond the tramline on off. Shoaib Bashir lets it go. The siren goes off as Bumrah has overstepped here.
Default_Commentary: 66.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Shoaib Bashir, No ball!

Commentary: Pace on this time, on a fuller length, on off, Shoaib Bashir stays rooted in his crease and pushes it from the crease to mid off.
Default_Commentary: 66.5: Jasprit Bumrah to Shoaib Bashir, No run.

Commentary: This is at 139.8 clicks, on a good length, a hint of away movement, Shoaib Bashir has a waft at the delivery away from his body. The ball nips away late and beats Bashir on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 66.6: Jasprit Bumrah to Shoaib Bashir, No run.

Commentary: Gets the ball to shape away from the left-hander, on a good length, outside off, Tom Hartley extends his arms and dabs it to a deepish cover-point.
Default_Commentary: 67.1: Mukesh Kumar to Tom Hartley, No run.

Commentary: Bowls it from much closer to the stumps and angles it away, on a back of a length, around off, Tom Hartley uses the pace of the delivery and runs it down to third man for a run.
Default_Commentary: 67.2: Mukesh Kumar to Tom Hartley, 1 run.

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Mukesh Kumar finally gets a wicket in this Test and he looks very relieved! Shoaib Bashir departs without troubling the scorers and India inch closer to a win! Mukesh bowls it full this time and makes the ball go away from the right-hander, on the sixth stump line, Shoaib Bashir could have left it alone but he prods forward to defend and pays the price. The ball nips away and catches the outside edge. The keeper, KS Bharat snaffles it safely for a straightforward catch.
Default_Commentary: 67.3: Mukesh Kumar to Shoaib Bashir, OUT! c KS Bharat b Mukesh Kumar.
Howout: c KS Bharat b Mukesh Kumar

Commentary: Swtiches back to around the wicket for Anderson and bowls it just outside off, on a good length, James Anderson has a tentative push at the delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Default_Commentary: 67.4: Mukesh Kumar to James Anderson, No run.

Commentary: And again! It leaves the batter again, on a good length, in the channel on off, James Anderson stays leg side of the ball and pokes at it, only to be beaten by the away movement.
Default_Commentary: 67.5: Mukesh Kumar to James Anderson, No run.

Commentary: FOUR! A proper top-order batter shot from England's number 11! Kumar gets the ball to angle back in this time, fuller and on middle, James Anderson gets on the front foot and shows the full face of the bat and drives it to the right of mid on for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 67.6: Mukesh Kumar to James Anderson, Four!

Commentary: Drops it short and on off, Tom Hartley goes back in his crease and cuts it wide of backward point for a single.
Default_Commentary: 68.1: Ravichandran Ashwin to Tom Hartley, 1 run.

Commentary: Fires it in from around the wicket, James Anderson pulls out the reverse sweep and hits it hard but straight to backward point.
Default_Commentary: 68.2: Ravichandran Ashwin to James Anderson, No run.

Commentary: Goes wide of the crease and slows it up as well, drags the length back a bit and bowls it on middle, James Anderson prods forward and keeps it out.
Default_Commentary: 68.3: Ravichandran Ashwin to James Anderson, No run.

Commentary: This is quicker through the air, fuller and on middle and leg, James Anderson gets his bat out in front of the pads and defends it on the leg side.
Default_Commentary: 68.4: Ravichandran Ashwin to James Anderson, No run.

Commentary: That could have gone anywhere! Ashwin tosses it up and bowls it full, on off, James Anderson goes for the reverse sweep again but swings a bit early. Gets it off the gloves and it lobs well over Rohit Sharma at first slip for a run.
Default_Commentary: 68.5: Ravichandran Ashwin to James Anderson, 1 run.

Commentary: FOUR! Nicely cut away! Shortens his length and bowls it closer to the off-stump line, Tom Hartley rocks back and cuts it late to get it right between backward point and short third man for a boundary.
Default_Commentary: 68.6: Ravichandran Ashwin to Tom Hartley, Four!

Commentary: Leg bye! Steams in from around the wicket and looks for the toe-crushing yorker, slips it down leg, on a full length, James Anderson fails to clip it away. The ball rolls off his pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
Default_Commentary: 69.1: Jasprit Bumrah to James Anderson, Leg bye.

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! THAT'S IT! All over for England! Jasprit Bumrah goes through the defence of Tom Hartley and finishes it off in his very own way! Stays around the wicket does Bumrah and bowls it on a hard length, slanting in, on the off-stump line, Tom Hartley stays put and looks to keep this one out with a straight bat. He shapes up to play for the ball angling in but this one nips away late and beats him all end up. It goes past the outside and clatters into the off-stump. Bumrah roars in delight to cap off what has been a Test to remember for him. All smiles in the Indian camp and the crowd will go home with smiles on their faces. India win by 106 runs and level the series at one game apiece!
Default_Commentary: 69.2: Jasprit Bumrah to Tom Hartley, OUT! b Jasprit Bumrah.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah
